Tonight I bring you a delivery story...

(at the new apartment complex right near us)

After about two minutes of progressively louder knocking on the apartment door, I call the number they give us if we need to contact the customer. The guy stammers for a second, and explains he must not have heard the knocking because he had his door closed. [halfway beliveable] ... then another minute or so passes... I get a call back from him... 
Customer, "Uh, dude, I'm not going to lie to you, ... i'm not at my house. I'm at winn-dixie, could you bring it there?"
At first this just strikes me as an unnessicarry lie, but then, I wonder how he could have possibly pulled it off even... 3rd floor apartment, no back door, I guess he could come running up the stairs, "yeah dude, my room was uh... over there... with the groceries...

Browsing wikipedia is one of my favorite ways to dodge doing homework.
This morning I was reading about Chattanooga, TN., which was the
hometown of the author of memoirs of a geisha, I followed some links to
read about yakuza ... name origin was quite interesting ... or
hachi-kyu-san, as most of you seeing this will probably already know
about the card game, i'll skip it =P. somehow it segue'd into iron
chef, which had an anlerfish tmed show, which brings this to the
factoid that inspired this post... 

[anglerfish have a unique mating method. Without light, finding a mate is a problem, especially at a
time when both individuals are ready to spawn. When scientists first
started capturing ceratioid anglerfish, they noticed that all of the
specimens were females. These individuals were a few inches in size and
almost all of them had what appeared to be parasites attached to them.
It turned out that these "parasites" were the males. When a male
anglerfish is hatched, he has extremely well developed olfactory organs
that detect scents in the water. He has no digestive system. His goal
in life is to detect the pheromones that the female anglerfish release.
When he finds a female, he bites into her flank which releases an
enzyme that digests the skin of his mouth and her body. The two then
fuse together, including blood vessels. The male degenerates into
nothing more than a pair of gonads that releases sperm when the female
releases hormones into the bloodstream that signals she is ready to
release her eggs.]

Definition:
Idiosyncrasy, n. - 1. A structural or behavioral characteristic peculiar to an individual or group; 2. A physiological or temperamental peculiarity; 3. An unusual individual reaction to food or a drug.

1. It is very hard for me to turn down something that is free, even stuff that I dont want or need.

This morning after work, there was this little orange kitten in the five-star parking lot. Apparantly its been hiding under one of the old broken down delivery trucks there for some time now, it was scrawny and skittish. You could tell it wanted affection by the way it watched people walk by... it would crawl out a little bit and flop down on its back or wag it's tail playfully. If called out to it would dart from car to car, edging closer as it circled about, untill it got within  arms reach, even if people wouldnt move, it would panic and run back to it's home under the old truck. It seemed to enjoy batting at gravel.
